Key technical points (implementation-ready):
- Rules: For each integer i in the sequence 1..n: if divisible by 3 output "Fizz"; if divisible by 5 output "Buzz"; if divisible by both 3 and 5 output "FizzBuzz"; otherwise output the number itself.
- Divisibility tests: use integer modulo operation; test both-conditions either by i % 15 == 0 or (i % 3 == 0 && i % 5 == 0).
- Input constraints: algorithm expects integer positive n. Non-integer inputs must be validated and rejected or coerced explicitly.
- Iteration pattern: single pass loop from 1 to n with constant-time checks per item.

